<md>I've fallen behind in EECS 16A course content since the week 9 lecture on Comparators and Op-Amps. I attempted to self-teach the material from Week 9 to Week 12 for MT2, but vastly underperformed on the exam. I plan on learning course material from week 9 until week 15 over the course of the next two weeks, running through practice exams once I know the material well, and clobbering MT2 with the final!

Are there any private tutors who would be interested in meeting 4-5 times weekly for the next two weeks to help me cover course content as linearly as possible? I would love to meet with the same tutor consistently. Both my schedule and payment is totally flexible :) </md>
